        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 2 at 4:07PM CDT until May 2 at 4:45PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>SVRSHV

The National Weather Service in Shreveport has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northern Jackson Parish in north central Louisiana...
Lincoln Parish in north central Louisiana...
Western Union Parish in north central Louisiana...
Northeastern Bienville Parish in northwestern Louisiana...
Claiborne Parish in northwestern Louisiana...

* Until 445 PM CDT.

* At 407 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line from
5 miles west of Gibsland to 10 miles southeast of Ruston, or along
a line from 10 miles southeast of Minden to 10 miles southeast of
Ruston, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Ruston, Grambling, Homer, Farmerville, Arcadia, Haynesville,
Bernice, Gibsland, Cooley, Dubach, Choudrant, Simsboro, Chatham,
Vienna, Athens, Lisbon, Eros, Downsville, Spearsville and Lillie.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. These storms are capable of producing damaging winds.</instruction>
